[{"id":"VR733476","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a curve labeled “Marginal Product” in the first and fourth quadrants of a plane with the origin labeled 0. The horizontal axis is labeled “Quantity of Labor,” and the values L sub 1, L sub 2, and L sub 3 are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Marginal Product of Labor.” The curve begins slightly above and to the right of the origin and moves upward and to the right and reaches its apex above the horizontal axis at L sub 1. The curve then moves downward and to the right, crosses the horizontal axis at L sub 2, and ends below the horizontal axis to the right of L sub 3.\" height=\"233\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR733476.g03.svg\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following will happen if the firm continues to hire additional units of labor beyond <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L sub 2\"><math alttext=\"L sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> in the short run?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR733476_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The firm’s marginal cost will decrease.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The firm will begin experiencing diminishing marginal returns.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The firm’s fixed cost will increase.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The average product of labor will be equal to zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The total product of labor will decrease.</p>"],"answer":4}]